<p>This is the first post on my blog. I’m Ray, a data scientist at Wallick Communities, and this site is where I’ll be writing about what I’m learning — mostly Python, SQL, and bits of the wider data ecosystem.</p>
<section id="what-to-expect" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="what-to-expect">What to expect</h2>
<p>A few categories of posts I’m planning:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Notes from learning Python</strong> — small things I had to figure out the hard way.</li>
<li><strong>Working with data</strong> — patterns I find useful for reports and analytics work.</li>
<li><strong>Tooling</strong> — the editors, libraries, and workflows I’ve settled on (and the ones I bounced off of).</li>
</ul>
<p>If a post helps you, I’d love to hear about it.</p>
</section>
